children.name: value
children.formal: The value of the measured amount. The value includes an implicit precision in the presentation of the value.

children.name: comparator
children.formal: How the value should be understood and represented - whether the actual value is greater or less than the stated value due to measurement issues. E.g. if the comparator is "<" , then the real value is < stated value.

children.name: units
children.formal: A human-readable form of the units.

children.name: system
children.short: System that defines coded unit form
children.formal: The identification of the system that provides the coded form of the unit.

children.name: code
children.formal: A computer processable form of the units in some unit representation system.
